<p>While Hurricane Sandy raged overhead, I decided to hack my apartment’s intercom (shh &mdash; don’t tell my former landlord). Soldering and coding through the rain and wind, with an <a href="https://electricimp.com/" target="_blank">Electric Imp</a>, a breadboard, and some basic components I became able to buzz my friends and myself in using either the physical button or a virtual button on a web app.</p>

<p>The project was an important learning experience. It was my first step toward later <abbr title="Internet of things">IOT</abbr> projects.</p>